name: Empanadas de Jamon y Roquefort (Ham and Roquefort Empanadas)
author: Fioa
summary: Quick and versatile empanadas made with ham and tasty Roquefort. Only 4 ingredients used for this gourmet finger food that your guests will love. Serve warm or cold.
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Grease 2 baking sheets with cooking spray
Arrange pastry discs on a flat work surface
Dab a little water around the rims
Place some ham and Roquefort cubes in the center; fold pastry over and press with a fork to seal
Transfer empanadas to the prepared baking trays
Brush beaten egg over the tops
Bake in the preheated oven until golden brown, about 20 minutes
